{"id":"10331","name":"Circular Progress Bar","tagline":"Generate PNG images for a circular progress bar with your fonts, colors, and dimensions","icon":"ios14 c4292093695 g61508","latest":"30213","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p><img alt=\"iOS 15: Works (iOS 15.0.2)\" src=\"https://atnbueno.com/ios15_ok.png\">\n<strong>iOS 15:</strong> Works (iOS 15.0.2)</p>\n<p>This shortcut is a function to generate a circular progress bar in PNG format with the percentage, font, colors, and dimensions indicated by the user.</p>\n<p><img alt=\"Thirty examples with different parameters\" src=\"https://atnbueno.com/circular-progress-bars.png\"></p>\n<p><strong>Modern CSS is awesome</strong> and inspired by the example at <a href=\"https://www.dottedsquirrel.com/circular-progress-css/\">https://www.dottedsquirrel.com/circular-progress-css/</a> I decided to do my own parametrized pure CSS version.</p>\n<p>When the shortcut is run directly (<em>demo mode</em>), it gives the user the option to change up to eight parameters:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>percentage</strong> is the value to show in the center of the circular progress bar</li>\n<li><strong>canvas</strong>, <strong>background</strong>, <strong>foreground</strong>, and <strong>text</strong> are the colors to use for each part</li>\n<li><strong>font</strong> is the font face for the percentage </li>\n<li><strong>outer-size</strong> and <strong>inner-size</strong> allow defining the size of both circles used</li>\n</ul>\n<p>With that input, the resulting image is displayed. If the shortcut is run from another shortcut (<em>function mode</em>) and the input is an equivalent dictionary, the image will be generated directly and will be the output of the shortcut, without any interaction with the user.</p>\n<p><img alt=\"A GIF made from images generated with this shortcut\" src=\"https://atnbueno.com/circular-progress-bar.gif\"></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Examples of valid colors: green, #0F0, #FF00FF, rgb(255, 0, 255)</li>\n<li>See https://developer.apple.com/fonts/system-fonts/ for typefaces available in iOS</li>\n<li>The original HTML+CSS code can also be found at <a href=\"https://gist.github.com/atnbueno/f5f7477443d39e46f0daebc855c8701f\">https://gist.github.com/atnbueno/f5f7477443d39e46f0daebc855c8701f</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Bonus:</strong> A slight modification to get the battery status in this format ðŸ™‚ <a href=\"https://www.icloud.com/shortcuts/d7c4a274c3444e349e58549c0d741244\">https://www.icloud.com/shortcuts/d7c4a274c3444e349e58549c0d741244</a></p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.0.2 - Oct. 19, 2021, 10:06 a.m.</strong></p><p>Fixed bug of some devices getting a half-pixel gap at the top and the bottom of the circle</p>"}